			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The aggro from crit affliction really isn't that bad, but it's definitely there.
<br />
Don't use that as an excuse for not buying it though. It's one of the best AAs we get.
<br />

<br />
I too have never been summoned and died on a raid from a crit tick at the beginning of the fight either. I've always organized my spell casting on raids though to compensate for a slacking tank at the beginning of the fight, or bad luck on weapon procs, and that seems to cover any extra dot crit aggro.
<br />

<br />
It would still be nice if they fixed it though. According to SOE this wasn't intended (or at least they didn't know about it), and any additional agro from foci wasn't either, though that's much harder to visibly see.
<br />

<br />
I believe a few people from both the necro and beastlord class forums did tests showing that there was extra aggro associated with crit ticks and presented it to SoE, but I haven't heard any news on that yet. Have they made any "official" response about it?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
